Bullwhip is a simple 2D game engine.
It is coded in C++, uses SFML2 for rendering, Box2D for physics, and Lua for scripting

Current Features:
State machine
Physics simulation intergrated with graphics
Supports most major image formats via SFML
It's very own level format
A fully moveable player!

Soon to come:
Menu system via GWEN
2D Skeletal animation
Networked players

